Description:
WB Residence On 767.6M2 Land In Residential Growth Zone
With a premier location and set on a grand allotment in this Residential Growth Zone precinct, this property is the ideal investment and development opportunity (subject to council approval). Perfectly positioned, this property is within walking from Keilor Plains train station, Keilor Downs Plaza, schools and easy access to freeways. The current property offers 2 bedrooms, spacious lounge with wall furnace, kitchen with air conditioner adjoins a spacious dining area, ample off street parking plus a carport and bonus 2 bedroom sleep out. Situated in the "Residential Growth Zone" these sought after allotments offer the ideal base for any unit or townhouse project (subject to council approval).

Description:
CALL THIS HOME!
This immaculate home combines position and potential and will appeal to a variety of astute home buyers. The warm and inviting interior comprises the best type of open plan living offering spacious lounge, flowing on from the lounge room is the well-appointed kitchen with AEG and Miele Appliances included. Adjoining light-filled meals area. Highly accommodating, there are 3 bedrooms and a central bathroom, Inclusions: additional separate powder room, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, LED downlights, High ceilings with decorative cornices, secure parking with lockable garage with rear access and a spacious courtyard/pergola. Additional features include electric roller shutters!
Only moments from all St Albans has to offer. With schools, train and bus services within walking distance, making this property the ideal perfect home.
First home? Low maintenance investment? Or downsizing, the choice is yours!
Inspection via Appointment ONLY!

Description:
A RENOVATED GEM!!
Team Abi from 361 Real Estate proudly presents to you this hugely renovated home in the most desired suburb of Kealba. Perfectly positioned and surrounded by parklands, and a choice of select schools, this surprisingly comfortable home is an exciting indoor/outdoor entertainer. There are 3 bedrooms in total, a modern bathroom, an impressive family lounge and dining room complimented by floorboards serviced by a large renovated stone top kitchen with stainless steel appliances and a dishwasher. The big backyard is enhanced with a covered entertainment area and low maintenance landscaping. Features include; shed, landscaped gardens, heating, , garage and carport for maximum parking space.
Lucky buyers can benefit from a serene, relaxing and convenient lifestyle, close to Brimbank Park, Green Gully Reserve, shops, cafes/restaurants and a short drive to popular shopping precincts.
Take advantage of this opportunity and call agents to organize an inspection today!!!

Description:
Exquisite Family Living!
This solid double-brick 5 bedroom residence in a very quiet court location oozes character and charm, with a flowing floor plan catering to your every need.
Sitting on a large 772 m2 allotment, you are within walking distance and in the zone of multiple schools including Keilor Downs College and Keilor Views Primary School. Keilor Central Shopping Centre, Watergardens Town Centre as well as Keilor Plains and Watergardens train stations are within easy reach as are major road networks including the Western Ring Road and Calder Freeway.
Features includes;
* 5 large fitted bedrooms (master with en suite and walk-in wardrobe)
* Separate study or 6th bedroom
* Spacious lounge room upon entry with atrium
* Meals area adjoining the kitchen with plenty of storage
* Cozy rumpus room with high ceilings, fireplace and in-built wet bar
* Bright and spacious central bathroom with twin vanity
* Large automatic double car garage with drive-through access
* Enormous driveway with extra parking spaces
* Large land size of approximately 772 m2
* Landscaped BBQ area perfect for entertaining
* Also includes evaporative cooling, ducted heating, air conditioner, solar panels, garden shed and many other quality fixtures and fittings

Description:
Sixties Classic with Gorgeous Garden Surrounds
Immaculately maintained by the one family since new (c1964), this attractive single-level home provides an environment of instant appeal along with a range of options for those looking to expand, renew or possibly redevelop (STCA) in one of Keilor East's favourite streets. Surrounded by arguably the best gardens in the suburb, the home's perfectly presented interior comprises three generous bedrooms (two with built-in robes) and spotless central bathroom, front lounge leading through to the dining area and adjoining kitchen. Features include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, additional split-system a/c (in the lounge), alarm system and security shutters all-round. Step outside to a wonderfully wide undercover entertaining area overlooking the spacious backyard complete with an amazing established garden, plus the added appeal of a garage/workshop and tandem double carport via gated side driveway. Walking distance to the open spaces of Rosehill Park, Phillip Road/Buckley Street buses and Milleara Shopping Centre, it's also close to popular primary and secondary schools, as well as easy freeway access.

Description:
Family Expanse with Big Block Credentials
Situated on one of Keilor Park's largest corner allotments (approx 802sqm), this well-presented home provides a wonderfully spacious and versatile family environment along with outstanding potential to modernize and personalize in the future. Well-proportioned and filled with natural light, the home's expansive interior comprises five bedrooms (extra-large downstairs master with private ensuite), large study or sixth bedroom, main family bathroom and separate powder room. The front lounge and adjoining dining room lead through to the kitchen with dishwasher and spacious family/meals area. Other features of the home include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, motorized security shutters, large laundry and under-stair storeroom. Step outside to discover an undercover patio, expansive concrete-paved entertaining area and substantial backyard garden, plus the added appeal of an oversized remote-control double garage (via Swan Street) and large rooftop terrace above. A short stroll to local buses (on Erebus Street) and popular Fosters Road shopping village, it's close to Steele Creek trails and parkland, easy access to a range of schools as well as the convenience of Westfield Shopping Centre and the Calder Freeway.
